com.communote.common.util

Class VersionComparator

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.communote.common.util.VersionComparator
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    Comparator<String>

    public class VersionComparator
extends Object
implements Comparator<String>
    Comparator to compare versions in dot notation like 3.25.2 as used in semantic versioning. The last part can be interpreted as revision.
    Examples
    • compare(1.0, 1.0.1) returns a value < 0
    • compare(1.0.1, 1.0.1) returns 0
    • compare(1.0.1, 1.0) returns a value > 0
    Author:
    Communote GmbH - http://www.communote.com/

      • VersionComparator

        public VersionComparator()

      • VersionComparator

        public VersionComparator(boolean versionEndsWithRevision,
                         boolean numericIncreasingRevision)
        Constructor to fine-tune the handling of a revision in the version string
        Parameters:
        versionEndsWithRevision - If true, the last part of the version is always interpreted as revision
        numericIncreasingRevision - if versionEndsWithRevision is true, this parameter defines whether the revision is a numeric value which increases with every new revision. Only in this case the revision is compared.
        Since:
        3.5
